<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="H" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Herself" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Herself</orth> (in two words in O. Edd.) 1) she, or her, in her own person: <cit><quote>h. hath taught her love,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.1.174" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. II, 1, 174</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>trust my wife with h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 2.2.320" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. II, 2, 320</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. err 1.1.46" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. I, 1, 46</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 1.2.100" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I, 2, 100</bibl> etc.<lb />2) in her own person: <cit><quote>the fair soul h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.1.129" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. II, 1, 129</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 5.4.98" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. V, 4, 98</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.5.41" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. IV, 5, 41</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 3.2.60" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. III, 2, 60</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 4.4.75" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. IV, 4, 75</bibl> etc.
<lb />3) refl. pron. of the third person fem. sing.: <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.3.14" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. II, 3, 14</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 1.1.40" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. I, 1, 40</bibl> etc.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>